===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Vim yek moten-virayeshgar (text editor) ghavi va chand-manzoore ast baraye sakhtan va dastkari file-haye matni (text files).  Dar terminal kar mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `vim filename` --> 📝 Baz kardan ya sakhtan yek file ba name `filename`.
    🔹 `vim +n filename` --> 🔢 Baz kardan file va raftan be khatte `n`.
    🔹 `vim -o file1 file2` --> ↔️ Baz kardan chand file be soorate ofoghi (horizontally).
    🔹 `vim -O file1 file2` --> ↕️ Baz kardan chand file be soorate amoodi (vertically).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ vim myfile.txt

    🔹 Baz kardan ya sakhtan file-e `myfile.txt`.

    $ vim +10 mylog.log

    🔹 Baz kardan file `mylog.log` va raftan be khatte 10.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ vim

    🔹 Baz kardan Vim bedoon file-e khass.  Az inja mitoonid file jadid besazid ya file-haye dige ro baz konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    Vim is a powerful and versatile text editor used for creating and manipulating text files. It operates within the terminal.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `vim filename` --> 📝 Open or create a file named `filename`.
    🔹 `vim +n filename` --> 🔢 Open the file and go to line `n`.
    🔹 `vim -o file1 file2` --> ↔️ Open multiple files horizontally.
    🔹 `vim -O file1 file2` --> ↕️ Open multiple files vertically.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ vim myfile.txt

    🔹 Open or create the file `myfile.txt`.

    $ vim +10 mylog.log

    🔹 Open the file `mylog.log` and go to line 10.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ vim

    🔹 Opens Vim without a specific file. From here you can create new files or open existing ones.
